	'en',
	'377',
	'<p>This project is considered as the first disbursement by the Norwegian Government to the Peruvian Government associated with the DCI. It considers four components or results: 1) the Government of Peru has planned the implementation of Phase II of the JIU and has begun its execution efficiently, 2) the zoning and forest management in the San Martín and Ucayali regions has increased, 3 ) value of the increased forest in order to be more competitive against the activities that cause deforestation and forest degradation, and 4) control of illegal activities that cause deforestation and forest degradation has increased. The activities of this Project in San Martín included the participation of the Regional Government of San Martín and Indigenous Peoples in the design of the Implementation Plan for Phase II of the JIU, the titling of native communities, strengthening the forest zoning process, promoting the conformation of the regional forestry control and monitoring table, in addition to increasing the coverage of conditional direct transfers for the conservation of forests in favor of native communities.</p>',
	null,
	'Preparing the way for the implementation of the Transformation Phase of the Joint Statement of Intent signed by the Governments of the Republic of Peru, the Kingdom of Norway and the Federal Republic of Germany'
);
