	'378',
	'en',
	'378',
	'<p>This project is considered as the first disbursement by the Norwegian Government to the Peruvian Government associated with the DCI. It considers four components or results: 1) the Government of Peru has planned the implementation of Phase II of the JIU and has begun its execution efficiently, 2) the zoning and forest management in the San Martín and Ucayali regions has increased, 3 ) value of the increased forest in order to be more competitive against the activities that cause deforestation and forest degradation, and 4) control of illegal activities that cause deforestation and forest degradation has increased. Activities in Loreto included titling of native communities, participation of the Regional Government of Loreto in the design of the Implementation Plan for Phase II of the JIU, the affiliation of new communities to the direct transfers conditioned by the National Program for the Conservation of Forests for Mitigation of Climate Change, among other activities.</p>',
